OL,6,GThe final editions of Look East from
OL,7,GCambridge and South Today from Oxford
OL,8,Gwere emotional affairs.
OL,10,FMake no mistake ` nobody at the BBC
OL,11,Freally wanted these programmes to end.
OL,12,FThe decision was driven by financial
OL,13,Fnecessity.
OL,15,FYes, there is an important argument
OL,16,Fabout the need to invest in online
OL,17,Fcontent. But in different circumstances
OL,18,Fit would not have meant scaling back
OL,19,Fsignificantly on the regional TV news.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G1/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34902
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FThe two services were relatively recent
OL,7,Faffairs, unlike some of the other
OL,8,Fregional news programmes.
OL,10,FThe Oxford opt came about when the
OL,11,Funwieldy "London and South East" region
OL,12,Fwas split up just over 20 years ago.
OL,13,FThe Cambridge programme developed out
OL,14,Fof a sub-opt from Look East.
OL,16,FThe changes were designed to improve
OL,17,Fregional news provision and make it
OL,18,Fmore relevant to viewers.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G2/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34903
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FThe problem with many English regions
OL,7,Fis that they do not reflect natural
OL,8,Fcommunities or administrative regions `
OL,9,Fthey essentially reflect transmitter
OL,10,Fservice areas.
OL,12,FThe extra services were designed to
OL,13,Freduce this problem and bring the
OL,14,Fprogrammes closer to their viewers.
OL,16,FThe collective ratings for the 6.30pm
OL,17,Fprogrammes across the UK are a reminder
OL,18,Fof just how important the service is.
OL,19,FOften the collective ratings are the
OL,20,Fbiggest of the day across any channel.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G3/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34904
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FThe challenge for Look East and South
OL,7,FToday now is to try to produce
OL,8,Fprogrammes relevant to the whole of
OL,9,Ftheir areas. There will still be
OL,10,Fstories and reports from the areas
OL,11,Fcovered by the Oxford and Cambridge
OL,12,Fprogrammes.
OL,14,FBut rather than endless salami slicing
OL,15,Fand axing, is it time to have a bigger
OL,16,Fdebate about what the BBC is for?
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G4/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34905
SC,0005
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FNobody would dispute that news and
OL,7,Fcurrent affairs is at the
OL,8,Forganisation's centre or that people
OL,9,Fwant and need reliable local news.
OL,10,FReaching younger audiences is hard too
OL,11,Fwhich is one reason online is so
OL,12,Fimportant.
OL,14,FBut unless BBC funding grows in real
OL,15,Fterms again, more awful decisions which
OL,16,Fnobody wants are inevitable.
OL,18,FHere are some things to ponder.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G5/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34906
SC,0006
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FRadio 1 and Radio 2 serve big
OL,7,Faudiences. Their playlists are very
OL,8,Fdifferent to some commercial services.
OL,9,FBut are they distinctive enough from
OL,10,Fthe market or merely ad free?
OL,12,FRadio 2, for example, has far less live
OL,13,Fand specialist music than it used to
OL,14,Fhave. These programmes used to dominate
OL,15,Fthe evenings and weekends.
OL,17,FSome of the digital radio services are
OL,18,Fdistinctive but could also be
OL,19,Fconsidered niche.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G6/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34907
SC,0007
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FOn TV, are there too many programmes
OL,7,Fthat fail to add sufficient value? It
OL,8,Fisn't that, say, some morning TV
OL,9,Fprogrammes are bad or aren't enjoyed.
OL,10,FBut do they drain resources away from
OL,11,Fmore important output?
OL,13,FWe have discussed before whether
OL,14,FEastEnders still merits the resources
OL,15,Fit receives.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G7/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34908
SC,0008
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FNobody is arguing here that the BBC
OL,7,Fdoesn't need to do popular, mainstream
OL,8,Fprogrammes. From Strictly to SAS Rogue
OL,9,FHeroes, the BBC can and does commission
OL,10,Fdistinctive output of high quality
OL,11,Fwhich gets big ratings. This must
OL,12,Falways be part of the mix.
OL,14,FBut it's maybe time to have to accept
OL,15,Fthat being all things to all people is
OL,16,Fimpossible without more money.
OL,18,FThe most important things about the BBC
OL,19,Fare the things which make it truly
OL,20,Fspecial.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G8/10
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34909
SC,0009
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1673184216
OL,6,FCutting the regional news service while
OL,7,Fhighly paid DJs are keeping Radio 1 and
OL,8,FRadio 2 going might not seem the best
OL,9,Foverall use of resources.
OL,11,FThe Wheel is a highly entertaining and
OL,12,Fwell-made quiz show. But is the prize
OL,13,Fmoney excessive for a publicly funded
OL,14,Forganisation? After all, part of the
OL,15,Ffun of Blankety Blank is its modest
OL,16,Fprizes. (Yes the money is a drop in the
OL,17,Focean but it all adds up.)
OL,19,FNobody who cares for the BBC wants it
OL,20,Fto abandon any service or programme
OL,21,Fwhich is enjoyed or valued.
OL,3,CStriving to be all things to all people
OL,4,Cnot possible with current BBC funding
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G9/10
